<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<section xml:id="where-to-learn" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Where to learn?</title>
  <subsection xml:id="subsec-courses">
    <title>Courses?</title>
    <p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p>
            What classes are provided? What are they about? How do they organize into a system?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            What classes are required for majors you're thinking about? What classes are required across majors?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            What are some official suggestions on math classes? What suggestions or comments do you hear from other people? What are the critics?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            What are the components of a class? Where to find syllabi and textbooks? How fast and difficult are the courses? What are the concerns about classes?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            What are some resources of tutoring available? Whom to ask for help about math classes?
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </p>
  </subsection>
  <subsection xml:id="subsec-websites">
    <title>Websites?</title>
    <p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p>
            What are some websites hosting online courses about linear algebra? What are the ratings and comments?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            What are some playlists teaching linear algebra? What are some content creators talking about linear algebra?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            What are some blogs and online articles about linear algebra? Are there interesting memes about linear algebra?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            What are some interactive demonstrations about linear algebra? How and how well do they explain concepts?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            What are some Q&amp;A forums answering math questions? What are the guidelines on asking questions?
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </p>
  </subsection>
  <subsection xml:id="subsec-libraries">
    <title>Libraries?</title>
    <p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p>
            What are the libraries here? Which library has math books?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            How to search for books and materials through the libraries? How to access electronic resources?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            How do the libraries circulate course materials?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            What are some books in the library about linear algebra? What are some online books about linear algebra that we have access to?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Where to look for comments and ratings on books or textbooks? Are there any highly recommended on books or book series? What are their weak points?
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </p>
  </subsection>
  <subsection xml:id="subsec-showcase-books">
    <title>Showcase: books</title>
    <p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p>
            Find out the library that contains math books. Visit the library in person.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Choose a math topic (not necessarily linear algebra). Find the shelves containing related books.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Look for comments online. Pick several books. Compare and choose the book that you can get out of the most.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Borrow the book, bring it to class and share! Show your book and explain the reason why you chose it.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </p>
  </subsection>
</section>
